metadata.title: Beechcraft Super King Air
aws::graph::propositions: # Beechcraft Super King Air 200 and 300 Series Variants
Model 200 is a variant of the Beechcraft Super King Air.
Model 200 was the prototype and initial production version of the Beechcraft Super King Air.
858 Model 200 aircraft were built including those converted to Model 200Ts.
The first prototype of Model 200 was converted to PD 290 jet aircraft.
The first three production aircraft of Model 200 were delivered to United States Army as Model A100-1s.
Model A200 is a variant of the Beechcraft Super King Air.
Model A200 was the first model purpose-built for United States military.
Model A200 was built for the United States Army and United States Air Force.
75 Model A200 aircraft were built.
Model 200T is a variant of the Beechcraft Super King Air.
Model 200T featured optional wingtip fuel tanks.
Model 200T featured optional dome-shaped side windows in the rear fuselage.
Model 200T had a modified belly to allow aerial photography.
The prototype and subsequent Model 200T aircraft were converted from Model 200s.
Model 200T aircraft were re-serialled after conversion.
23 Model 200T aircraft were delivered.
Model A200C is a variant of the Beechcraft Super King Air.
Model A200C was the second military model built for United States military.
Model A200C was built for the United States Navy and United States Marine Corps.
Model A200C featured a cargo door in the left-hand rear fuselage.
90 Model A200C aircraft were built.
Model 200C is a variant of the Beechcraft Super King Air.
Model 200C is the civil equivalent to Model A200C.
36 Model 200C aircraft were built.

text:
## Variants
In roughly chronological order, the 200 and 300 Series King Air variants and production numbers are:

Model 200
Prototypes and initial production version, 858 built including those converted to Model 200Ts; first prototype was converted to PD 290 jet aircraft and first three production aircraft were delivered to U.S. Army as Model A100-1s.
Model A200
First model purpose-built for U.S. military (Army and Air Force), 75 built.
Model 200T
Version with optional wingtip fuel tanks, optional dome-shaped side windows in the rear fuselage, and modified belly to allow aerial photography. Prototype and subsequent aircraft converted from Model 200s and re-serialled; 23 delivered.
Model A200C
Second military model built for U.S. Navy and USMC with cargo door in LH rear fuselage, 90 built.
Model 200C
Civil equivalent to A200C, 36 built.
